help.default: MIN 0 MAX 2147483647  For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; this variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP addresses and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP address.

createwithdefault.description: Attribute used to tell the cli whether an object can be created withdefaultref and/or default settings.  If this is false, all attributes must be set by user in order for create to be called.

defaultref.description: Object which contains defaults for the given object, the common case will be a global object.  Flexswitch Model may have defaults set in model they will be overwriten by what is defined here. If default is not set in model or defaultref, then a 0 (int), true (bool) and '' (string) will be used. This attribute will also be used on a deletion of an attribute within an object.  A 'no attribute' will set the attribute back to default

objname.description: object name to which references these attributes
